						<summary>

						<p>On the wall of the east inner <hi rend="italic">gōpura,</hi> Śvētāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 10: 981 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of ninety sheep for a perpetual lamp to the god of Tiruveṇkāḍu by Ārūraṉ Ambalattaḍigaḷār, the queen of Uttama-chōḷa. The <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> agreed to protect this charity.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 257. </p>						

